			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=12456#M12456">5</a> of 8
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 358 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>I started out on TZ, at the height of its popularity, and watched it steadily decline.&nbsp; I watched that decline accelerate when pop came out and the most advanced guild on the server was able to block others from getting flagged and progressing.&nbsp; That experience is part of the reason that I said that PvP should be a way to advance your character, not just a way to keep others from advancing.&nbsp; The way things are, a top guild can block the advancement of others with no real risk, because you can't go backwards by engaging in PvP.&nbsp; If there was experience, and especially gear loss (even no-trade gear) as the result of a PvP death, you wouldn't end up with stagnation at the top.&nbsp; There would always be those trying to take down those who were higher up, not just to grief them, but to advance themselves.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Right now, just about all PvP on Zek is people running around looking for easy kills, and insta-gating or running for a book when they lose the upper-hand.&nbsp; The incentive is to PvP down (those weaker than you), because the only bragging rights are in kill streaks and PvP points.&nbsp; If you could truly advance your character through PvP, the bragging rights would be in leveling up and getting better gear by killing those higher than you (through better skill).&nbsp; There would be no point at all in ganking weaker just because you can, and little incentive to do so just to block their advancement.&nbsp; You're too busy trying to advance yourself.</P>
<P>If they started a progression server with any variant of the current rules, it would just become Zek all over again in short order.&nbsp; A progression server by itself isn't the answer to good PvP on EQ.&nbsp; Some real design thought needs to go into making PvP sustainable and fun for those outside the small core group that plays 20 hours a week or more.</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>07-08-2006</span> <span class=time_text>10:45 AM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
