			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
MelindhraZek wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>&nbsp;pvp in those other games is simply better designed and implemented in them than it is in EQ.&nbsp;<BR></P>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>On this statement I have to disagree with you. I have played most of the PvP "designed" games out there, and I have to say EQ's PvP system (at least pre-Luclin) was one of the best systems for PvP out there. Fights didnt end in less than 30 seconds, thus allowing for some thought, and strategy. In a longer protracted fight you had to know not only your class, but also your oponants(sp). You also needed to be prepared (things like having the right spells up for cetain classes ie Flame Lick to combat mez -if you were a Ranger that is- or having the right potions in your bag) You could actually use strategy like using terain (sp) retreat and heal, then continue the fight. Gear pre-Luclin wasnt the sole determining factor, you could beat someone in top tier gear, even if you were not equally equiped....just took a skill, and knowledge of your class and their's. As compared to WoW for example (as it is the most "popular" game right now and was "designed" for PvP) where you have 15 to 30 seconds to push a few buttons....no jousting, barely time to consume a potion, ect. Also world PvP in games like CoH and WoW are nearly dead (non existant in CoH's case) and PvP is confined to instanced games like capture the flag. No I have to say that EQ was one of the best PvP enabled games ever...maybe not the best, but definately up there near the best.<BR>	
